p: \bThanks for coming, \pn. You've arrived just in time.
\bPeople have seen both Registeel and its Delta counterpart all over the mountain!
\bWe've done some calculations... they should be passing by any moment now.
\bProfessor Pine was kind enough to let me borrow Holon University's last few Master Balls to catch them.
\rWait, what ? You told me you were using it for a drinkin-
\bWow, that was... absurdly easy and anticlimactic.
\bMaster Balls... really take all the fun and excitement over catching a Pokemon away, don't they?
\bIt's a wonder they even exist at all.
\rThis is a legendary Pokemon! The type of Pokemon who control our ecosystems, the weather, even time and space!
\rNot only should any one person not have this power, but who knows what kind of impact the removal of such an important species will have on the ecosystem!
\bYou're absolutely right, Pine.\nI promise you, when we're done researching, I'll release it.\nI only want the best for everyone!
\rYou better follow through, or I really will have your tenure revoked.
\bOh, she can't cut my tenure if I'm the owner of the university.
\bNobody can cut my tenure if I'm the owner of the world!
\bIt's so incredible to think that I'm holding a legendary Pokemon...
\bI really believe in these Deltas. These are the future.
\bBut I AM going to catch all three members of this trio.
\bYou said you found Regice and its counterpart underneath the lake?
\bOr DO try and stop me! Bwahahahaha!
\bYou can't stop the tide of Delta Species, pun intended.
Battle: \bI've been hearing that Registeel's been wandering the region.\nAnd Professor Maple thinks there might be a Delta Registeel too... crazy!
EndSpeech: I hope I can find something rare.
EndBattle: \bI hope I can find something rare.

EndSpeech: Actually, I should probably just leave. Makes more sense, y'know?
